Five-Year Accident History



Within the past five years, Garland Logistics Pointe has not had any accidental releases that resulted in injuries or property damage. The plant has maintained an excellent safety record throughout its operating history and has never had a major anhydrous ammonia release that could have had adverse effects on the public.  



Emergency Response



In the event that an ammonia release does occur, Garland Logistics Pointe has an emergency action plan that coordinates emergency response with the Garland Fire Department. If such a release did occur, plant personnel would contact the Garland Fire Department, who would dispatch specially trained personnel to the facility. 



